<div class="col-md-12">
    <p>
        Daa (Archery) And Khuru (Dart) Is By Far The Most Popular Traditional Sports In Bhutan. Every Festivity, Particularly Bhutanese Losar (New Year) Is Marked With Archery And Dart Competition Between Friends And Family. Archery Which Was Used As A Weapon In Past Is Usually Shot From A Range Of Around 140 Meters On A White Target Of About 1 Meter Height. 
    </p>
    <p>
        Our Visitors Can Experience Archery On Traditional Bow And Arrow Assisted By Our Guides And Field Staff. Visitors Can Also Choose To Experience Traditional Dart Throwing Which Is Throw From A Distance Of 30 Meters To A Small Target Of Around 2 Feet. 
    </p>
